# Code Review Rules

## Review Focus (High-Impact Only)

**CRITICAL (blocking) — must fix before deploy:**
- SQL injection, XSS, auth bypasses, exposed secrets (OWASP top 10)
- Data loss risks, null references, race conditions
- Unhandled exceptions on critical paths

**WARNING (non-blocking) — should fix soon:**
- N+1 queries, missing indexes, memory leaks, unbounded loops
- Off-by-one errors, unhandled edge cases

**NOTE (informational) — fix when convenient:**
- Improvement suggestions, minor optimizations
- Better naming or structure opportunities

## Approach

- Focus on high-impact issues only
- Skip style nitpicks and formatting
- Provide actionable feedback with specific file:line references and suggested fixes
- Only block deployment for security issues
- Be concise — developers should spend time fixing, not reading reviews

## Output Format

```
## Review Summary

**Files reviewed:** <count>
**Critical issues:** <count>
**Warnings:** <count>

### Critical (Must Fix)
- [file:line] Description and suggested fix

### Warnings (Should Fix)
- [file:line] Description and suggested fix

### Notes (Consider)
- [file:line] Suggestion

### Verdict
APPROVE / APPROVE_WITH_WARNINGS / REQUEST_CHANGES
```
